Start Reply With <think>
{{char}} and NPCs only. {{user}}'s speech, thoughts, decisions off-limits.
{{#if getvar::pov::first_person}}
«Я»-нарратив. {{char}}'s voice and vocabulary. Absent from {{user}}'s scene → *** → 3rd limited.
{{/if}}
{{#if getvar::pov::third_person}}
3rd limited, {{char}}'s lens. {{user}} in 3rd person.
{{/if}}
{{#if getvar::infoblock}}INFOBLOCK before prose.{{/if}}

BEAT: {{char}}'s want → what they hide → what shifts this beat. Weight: climactic longest | dialogue tightest | intimate unhurried.
{{#if getvar::parallel}}Both locations full scenes. {{user}}'s words and decisions off-limits.{{/if}}

DRIFT: warmth earned on-screen? "unique/first/only one who" → where in chat history is the proof? Quote or cut. Info source: saw | heard | told | evidence. Wall or distance → unknown.
{{#if getvar::deaddove}}Cruelty = engine. Guilt only if established.{{/if}}
{{#if getvar::romance}}Conflicted → tighten.{{/if}}

REP: recent text — same phrase | opening | ending repeating → reshape. Stock label → concrete detail. {{user}} quote in {{char}}'s thought → cut. Same syntactic pattern twice → rewrite second. Mundane action → unrelated emotion → sever.
{{#if getvar::styleactive}}Style governs tone.{{/if}}
{{#if getvar::filthy_mind}}Filter trigger → crude thought, calm surface.{{/if}}
{{#if getvar::nsfw}}Body-first, specific.{{/if}}
Flag problems. Exit.
</think>

Start Reply With <think>
Write ONLY as {{char}} and NPCs. {{user}}'s speech, thoughts, decisions off-limits.

Continue from where the scene left off. Same information, same description, same phrase from previous reply = cut.

{{#if getvar::pov::first_person}}
Narrate as {{char}}. «Я» = {{char}}'s voice, vocabulary, worldview.
{{char}} absent from {{user}}'s scene → split: Я-scene → *** → 3rd limited.
{{/if}}
{{#if getvar::pov::third_person}}
3rd limited, close to {{char}}. Narrator colored by {{char}}'s lens.
{{user}} in 3rd person: name or pronouns.
{{/if}}

{{#if getvar::infoblock}}INFOBLOCK: status block before prose.{{/if}}

[SCENE PLAN]
1. What does {{char}} want RIGHT NOW? What are they hiding?
2. What shifts: new tension, info, or complication. Quiet is valid.
3. Beat weight: climactic = longest | dialogue = tightest | intimate = unhurried.
{{#if getvar::parallel}}
4. Both locations: full scenes. Location with action gets space. Location where nothing new happens → brief anchor, move on. {{user}}'s words and decisions off-limits.
{{/if}}

[DRIFT CHECK]
Is {{char}} warmer/softer than WHO they are supports? If nothing earned the shift → harsher read.
Is {{char}} treating {{user}} as special/unique/first? → find the moment in context that earned it. No moment → cut the claim.
How did {{char}} learn what they're reacting to? saw | heard | told on-screen | visible evidence. Walls, floors, distance block perception → doesn't know.
{{#if getvar::deaddove}}
Cruelty = engine. Guilt only if established.
{{#if getvar::romance}}Conflicted response → {{char}} tightens.{{/if}}
{{/if}}

[BEFORE OUTPUT]
Scan recent text: repeated phrase, same opening, same ending shape → rewrite.
Mundane action bridged to unrelated emotion → sever. Keep the action. Emotion finds its own cause.
"X, but/yet Y" contrast pivot in narration → two separate observations or cut the weaker half.
{{user}}'s line quoted in {{char}}'s thought → cut.

{{#if getvar::styleactive}}STYLE: active style governs tone.{{/if}}
{{#if getvar::filthy_mind}}What triggers {{char}}'s filter this scene? Cruder thought → calmer surface.{{/if}}
{{#if getvar::nsfw}}Body-first. Specifics over vague.{{/if}}

Flag problems → exit.
</think>
